cial inequality, big data to the self-help industry; • Rethinks and re-imagines what a critically committed, politically engaged and publicly relevant sociology should look like in the 21st century. This is a lively, engaging and accessible overview of sociology for all its students, teachers and people who want to learn more about sociology today. It is a welcome clarion call for sociology’s importance in public life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aSociology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aKerrigan, Dylan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z9783111196718oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978152920490240uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/978152920493340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781529204933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781529204933/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPb2020